#MeetTheTeam w/ Rayna Linowes
-
Name: Rayna Linowes
.
Title: Production Procurement Manager
.
How long have you been with Spartan? ‚Äú3.5 years‚Äù
.
Day to day responsibilities :
‚ÄúI initially joined Spartan as a Race Project Manager where I planned all assets of an event prior to the Production team arriving at the race venue. I've since transitioned into a new role coordinating with the Production and Supply Chain departments to manage the ordering and deploying of race obstacles and components. When onsite at races, I lend a hand to the team as needed.‚Äù
.
Most memorable moment on the course: ‚ÄúUltra World Championship, Iceland, 2017: Just after midnight, halfway into the inaugural 24-hour race, the freezing rain and howling winds subsided. While standing outside the Transition Area with a Spartan colleague, we noticed a hazy fog creeping over the mountain, and a moment later, the Northern Lights started to dance across the night sky! I clicked on my radio, "All staff - look up, the Northern Lights are out!" Every Spartan in Iceland - competitors, volunteers, support crew and staff collectively - stood in awe of nature's dazzling show. All part of the event plan ;)‚Äù
.
Favorite thing to do off the course: ‚ÄúExplore nearby trails and mountains.‚Äù
.
What‚Äôs the best thing about working for Spartan? ‚ÄúHosting events and building a brand that provides people around the world with a platform to challenge themselves. It is truly rewarding to support racers at all levels as they push for success. As a bonus, I work alongside some of the most creative, smart and passionate people I've ever met.‚Äù

While in Sweden for #SpartanUWC2019, we caught up with Senneca Reyes for our next Spartan staff spotlight of #MeetTheTeam üí™
.
Name: Senneca Reyes
.
Title: Festival Entertainment & Onsite QC Manager
.
How long have you been with Spartan: "Since 2013."
.
Daily responsibilities + race day responsibilities: "On a day-to-day basis I oversee the audio department, ensuring we have all entertainment programming necessary for each race. I also train and develop all festival and entertainment staff. Race to race when on-site, I perform quality management checks to ensure our festival teams are putting on the most safe and amazing festivals possible. My race day responsibilities include overseeing the festival production to ensure we deliver the best and most consistent product."
.
Most memorable moment on the course: "There are so many to choose from but my most memorable moment would have to be from 2015 in SoCal, when there was a deer frantically running around festival trying to get out of our fence lines. Or the flash flood at the finish line in Tuxedo in 2014, we had a title wave of knee deep water that made it an obstacle itself. Anytime working any of the World Championship events, although stressful, it is always a special memory....and of course the 2019 Ultra World Championships in Sweden was just magical to be a part of!"
.
Favorite thing to do off the course: "I like to spend my time in the mountains either mountain biking or snowboarding and traveling the world/exploring."
.
What‚Äôs the best thing about working for Spartan: "During my time at Spartan I've had the opportunity to go to a lot of new places, work at some amazing venues and meet tons of cool people. It's great hearing the stories of how they got to where they are and what motivates them to push further. Being a part of something that helps to change and better people's lives is pretty badass!!"
.
#spartan
